Scope: Hiding Information
    People should be able to access your interface, the functionality you make public, and not be concerned with your 
    implementation, how you program that functionality
    
    Local variables can only be accessed from the scope that they originated in
    You can modify a variable within a function to change its scope
    
    Constructor functions: Constructors are functions that streamline the common process of creating objects with similar
    properties and methods. You call a constructor by using the new keyword.
    If you want to make private data members objects, then you can put them in a function
